->It is an hook that lets to manage side effects in a functional component
->It can be used only in top level of the component or custom hook
	useEffect(setup,dependency);
->useEffect returns undefined
->It takes two arguments , a setup function that manages the side effect logic and a dependency list array.
->The setup function also returns a cleanup function
->The dependency list should contain all the reactive values used in the setup function->Reactive values include state, props and all the variables and functions declared inside the component.
->When you update the state inside the Effect , and add the state to the dependency list it will cause infinite render
->If the dependency list is not provided, useEffect logic will be executed on every render and if the empty array is provided it will execute only at initial mounting time.
->If the dependency list is provided with reactive values , then whenever it changes , after the re-render useEffect logics will be executed.
->If the dependency list includes the function or objects created inside the component , during each time of rendering a new copy of the the function or object will be created and thus even though these object and functions are not changed , it will cause the useEffect logic to execute.
